10. What happens if an exception occurs inside a catch block?
-->Answer:
If an exception occurs inside a catch block and it is not handled, the exception propagates to the calling method or JVM.

Example:
try {
   int a = 10/0;
}
catch(Exception e) {
   int b = 10/0;
}

Here:
- First exception is handled
- Second exception occurs inside catch block
- JVM terminates program if second exception is not handled

